Les vrais pourtraits et vies des hommes illustres offer a glimpse of France during a time of great upheaval. Originally published in 1584, Thevet's collection contains over two hundred biographical sketches, detailing the lives of important persons from antiquity to the sixteenth century. Edward Benson and Roger Schlesinger have translated and annotated Thevet's portraits of his contemporaries, and divided them into three categories: monarchs, aristocrats, and scholars. Additionally, an extensive introduction places the work in context and describes the critical attention that Thevet and his writings have received. Together these portraits provide a history of sixteenth-century France as the country underwent tremendous change: from an intellectual renaissance and its first encounter with the New World to the Protestant Reformation and the Wars of Religion that followed. France was irrevocably altered by these events and Thevet's account of the lives of individuals who struggled with them is indispensable.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aRenaissancezFrancevBiography. 7aHISTORY / Europe / France.2bisacsh1 aBenson, Edward, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBenson, Edward.1 aRabb, T. K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchlesinger, Roger, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchlesinger, Roger, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014z978311074526940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780271090719zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271090719423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780271090719.jpg  a978-3-11-074526-9  Penn State University 